eu.toolchain.concurrent

Interface Completable<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of the value being completed
    All Superinterfaces:
    Stage<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConcurrentCompletable

    public interface Completable<T>
extends Stage<T>
    A value that can be completed at a later point in time. In general this follows the contract of Stage, but extends to to allow for the completion of the underlying computation.
    See Also:
    Stage
